From that it is clear that "div based" algo is about 6 times slower compared to "sum based"  . With div based algo, it is about ~7ms for 1mn aggregations compared to ~1ms for sum based , and that might make a difference for some users but not most.
I think, for the mean aggregator introduced here, we can have both algos be present in the code with `div based` being the default but ability to switch to `sum based` if need be.

